        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The year is given by the reference to <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_6589.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Reichenbach 1852</ref> (see n. 7, below).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">The letter from Lindley has not been found. It was presumably a response to the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-3289.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to John Lindley, 18 October [1861]</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3">Of the seven tribes of orchids described in <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_4776.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Lindley 1853</ref>, the Arethuseae was the only tribe members of which CD was unable to examine.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f4">James Veitch, a Chelsea nurseryman, supplied CD with many species of exotic orchids.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f5">See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-3316.xml" resp="#mjhawkins" cert="high">letter to Dorothy Fanny Nevill, 12 November 1861</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f6"><ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_4119.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Sigismund Rucker</ref>, West Hill, Wandsworth, is acknowledged several times in <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_6010.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Orchids</hi></ref> for having ‘repeatedly’ sent CD valuable orchids (see especially <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_6010.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Orchids</hi></ref>, p. 158 n.).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f7">CD refers to <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_6589.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Reichenbach 1852</ref> (see letters to J. D. Hooker, <ref target="./DCP-LETT-3286.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">15 [October 1861]</ref>, <ref target="./DCP-LETT-3288.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">18 October [1861]</ref>, and <ref target="./DCP-LETT-3296.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">23 October [1861]</ref>).</note>
        </div>        
            
